doc.title: Wikipedia: Ahmad Reza Pourdastan
doc.abstract: Ahmad Reza Pourdastan (Persian: امیر سرتیپ احمدرضا پوردستان) is an Iranian general currently serving as commanding officer of the ground forces of the Iranian Army.<Ref>

doc.title: Wikipedia: ECS Electrochemistry Letters
doc.abstract: ECS Electrochemistry Letters is a monthly peer-reviewed scientific journal covering electrochemical science and technology. It was established in 2012 and is published by the Electrochemical Society.

doc.title: Wikipedia: Naděžda Koštovalová
doc.abstract: Naděžda Koštovalová (née Tomšová; born 10 September 1971 in TáborSports-Reference profile) is a retired Czech athlete who specialised in the 400 metres. She won a silver medal in the 4 x 400 metres relay at the 1995 World Indoor Championships.
